modules.description: This module provides functions to create and manipulate planar straight-line graphs (PSLGs) and triangulations, including reading and writing mesh data from files. It works with data types such as `Mesh.pslg`, `Mesh.t`, and associated point, segment, and region structures. Concrete use cases include generating 2D triangulated meshes from geometric input, defining regions and holes with specific orientations, and importing/exporting mesh data in the EasyMesh file format for simulation or visualization tasks.
